{"key":"post-12809697","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12809697</id>\n<content>You ideally don't want the weight to rattle.&amp;nbsp; When it does, it means you're releasing &lt;i&gt;excess&lt;/i&gt; pressure.&amp;nbsp; Control pressure with the stove burner, not the rocker, to keep water from boiling out.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You also should be using a trivet or a row of jar lid rings to keep the substrates off the bottom, not a towel.&amp;nbsp; There's a lot of ghetto things that get recommended around here, and the towel on the bottom is one of them.&amp;nbsp; You can easily fry your jars that way.&amp;nbsp; If you're doing 1/2 pint brf/pf jars, they should be elevated totally out of the water, which might take two rows of jar lid rings.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12809782</next>\n<prev>12809538</prev>\n<first>12802550</first>\n<last>12809905</last>\n<when>1277605486</when>\n<utime>06/27/10 05:24 AM</utime>\n</post>"}